      "content": "**Digital Communication:** Maintaining **professionalism** in digital correspondence requires acute attention to tone, always demonstrating **respect** for colleagues' time and **boundaries**. Before sending, review your message to ensure it upholds the highest standards of **professionalism** while respecting established communication **boundaries**. **Respect** for privacy is paramount when discussing sensitive matters.\n\n**Physical Workspace Etiquette:** Respecting shared office space means acknowledging the **boundaries** of others' focus time; noise levels directly impact **professionalism**. Always maintain a high degree of **respect** for colleagues' personal space and established work **boundaries**. A **professionalism** standard includes keeping shared areas tidy.\n\n**Meeting Conduct:** Effective meeting conduct demands **professionalism** from start to finish, requiring participants to respect the agenda and time **boundaries**. Showing **respect** means active listening, and clearly articulating your points while respecting others' input reinforces strong professional **boundaries**.",
